# Delivery Summary (mandatory after code changes)

When a task **changes code** (creates, edits, or deletes project files), end the final response with the section below.

**Skip** for Q&A, read-only exploration, reviews with no edits, or pure explanation tasks.

**Do not** run `git commit`, `git push`, or open a PR unless the user explicitly asks.

## Required closing format

```markdown
## Delivery summary

### PR Description
- [Specific change: file/feature/behavior — not generic filler]
- [Another concrete bullet if applicable]

### Suggested commit message
Imperative subject max 72 chars

Optional one-line why if it adds context.
```

## Rules

- **PR Description**: bullets only; name what changed (pages, APIs, components, config). No "improved code quality" without specifics.
- **Suggested commit message**: imperative mood (`Add`, `Fix`, `Update`), ≤72 char subject; body optional, one line max.
- Never auto-commit or auto-PR.
- If the task was read-only, omit this entire section.
